I have heard many a time that GM's and Guides are sorry and never get anything done. What most people dont realize is that there are usually 30-50 petitions in the queue at prime-time hours. Most of these taking anywhere from 1min to an hour to "solving". And Ive noticed players complaining that they never get their petitions answered. I can give an answer for this. A guide or GM checks out the petition and sees if the player is on. If not, they check the petition back in the queue. After three times, if the player is not on, the petition is deleted. I hope I have been informative and if you have any questions, dont hesitate to send me an e-mail.

Fuzpuz,
Ex Guide of the Venril Sathir server
(currently has a character on Rodcent Nife)

